flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn preserved archive history into closure-complete, replay-referenceable archive truth"]
    G2["Keep this path narrower than the full learning-input basis and narrower than later OFS dataset construction"]
    G3["Answer when preserved archive history becomes formally closed enough that later replay and learning can rely on it"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["The entry is not raw runtime events anymore"]
    E2["It is not merely that some archive objects exist"]
    E3["The entry is run-scoped archived runtime history plus the continuity metadata needed to prove that this archive surface is the one later lanes should trust"]
    E4["The archive connector handles pin not just the object-store prefix, but also the source topic, starting position, proof mode, and probe mode"]
    E5["The current closure contract expects archive history under archive/{platform_run_id}/events/ and uses object-path-plus-payload-readback as the run-scope proof mode"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Run-scoped archive objects plus continuity proof"]
    R2["Archive closure marker"]
    R3["Replay-reference resolution from spine closure"]
    R4["Downstream learning-input lane can trust the archive basis"]
    R5["Archive truth becomes closure-complete and replay-referenceable"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["The run-scoped archive object set"]
    C2["The continuity proof that ties the archive sink back to its source records"]
    C3["The archive closure marker"]
    C4["The replay-reference semantics that later lanes will read as source-offset ranges"]
    C5["Replay basis at learning-input closure must be pinned as source-offset ranges with explicit mode-aware meaning"]
    C6["The handles registry separately pins the archive connector's proof mode as object-path-plus-payload-readback"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform treats archive preservation and archive usability for replay as different owned truths"]
    L2["The system is not saying once objects land in object storage, later replay can figure it out"]
    L3["There is an explicit closure boundary where archive history becomes replay-referenceable"]
    L4["Later learning is blocked until that boundary is satisfied"]
    L5["That is strong A-level design signal"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["The archive surface is concretely pinned to archive/{platform_run_id}/events/"]
    S2["The current runtime contract for the archive lane is pinned to ECS batch-consumer-to-object-storage posture"]
    S3["The control topic is the source topic"]
    S4["The run-scope proof mode is object-path-plus-payload-readback"]
    S5["Explicit probe emit mode uses ECS MSK producer task"]
    S6["The current archive cutover closure says the lane only closed green after probe-to-sink continuity closure, where admitted probe ids were present in the run-scoped archive objects"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["The platform refused to equate archive sink wrote objects with archive closure is trustworthy"]
    Y2["The run-process requires archive-writer closure evidence at RTDL catch-up closure, not just activity"]
    Y3["The later learning-input gate requires archive plus replay references to be resolved from spine closure, not guessed from whatever files happen to be present"]
    Y4["The archive cutover closure shows the same attitude in implementation: the lane stayed fail-closed until it could prove probe-to-sink continuity under the run-scoped archive prefix"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The run-process closure law shapes it through RTDL catch-up closure: archive-writer closure evidence must be present and commit evidence must include archive closure marker"]
    X2["The learning-input law shapes it through learning-input closure: replay basis must be pinned as source-offset ranges with explicit mode-aware semantics, and learning cannot start until archive, labels, and replay references are resolved from spine closure"]
    X3["The archive connector contract shapes it concretely through the pinned run-scoped archive prefix, proof mode, source topic, and consumer settings"]
    X4["So this path is governed by archive-closure rules, replay-basis rules, and mode-aware source-offset semantics"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately adds another explicit truth boundary after archive writing"]
    T2["That costs more ceremony: closure evidence, closure marker semantics, replay-reference semantics, and a clear distinction between preserved history and replay-ready history"]
    T3["But that cost buys something important: later learning and replay lanes do not need to infer their basis from ad hoc object inspection"]
    T4["They can depend on a named closure outcome"]
    T5["The archive cutover closure makes this especially clear: the lane did not go green merely because the sink existed; it went green after runtime-path adjudication and probe-to-sink continuity closure"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, the platform can still preserve archive objects, append audit truth, and later attempt replay or learning"]
    N2["But it loses a clean answer to when the archive became closure-complete"]
    N3["It loses a clean answer to which replay references later lanes should trust"]
    N4["It loses a clean answer to whether replay basis came from spine closure or from informal guess"]
    N5["It loses a clean answer to whether learning-input closure is anchored to true archive basis or only to object presence"]
    N6["That would weaken A immediately because the system would preserve runtime history but have no explicit owner for turning that history into replay-referenceable basis"]
    N7["The run-process itself rejects that looseness by making archive closure and replay-reference resolution formal gates"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["Closed archive surface for the run"]
    O2["Replay-reference continuity is explicit enough that downstream learning-input closure can bind to it"]
    O3["This path stops once archive truth is closure-complete and replay-referenceable"]
    O4["Owned outcome: replay-referenceable archive truth"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a distinct job for turning preserved archive history into replay-referenceable closure truth"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>replay references are not inferred opportunistically; they are resolved from spine closure under explicit gate semantics"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>the path is concretely seated in the run-scoped archive prefix, the pinned archive connector contract, and the archive-closure marker requirement"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>this path is governed by archive-closure rules, replay-basis rules, and mode-aware source-offset semantics"]
    A5["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>the current wired route only counts as closed when continuity proof is explicit, which is why the archive cutover lane was pinned to probe-to-sink continuity rather than vague archive looks okay posture"]
    A6["A-level meaning:<br/>preserved archive history becomes formally trustworthy replay basis instead of leaving later learning and replay to guess from object presence"]
  end

